{
  "text": "In the current experiment, data from a cued auditory spatial at tention task [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] were reanalyzed with respect to oscillatory activity in the alpha band on both the sensor as well as source level. The main goal of the study was to investigate whether auditory alpha activity is modulated by the validity of a preceding acous tic cue. In a second step, we were interested to what extent ef fective connectivity is altered between relevant auditory and nonauditory nodes within the context of auditory spatial atten tion during the cue target period. Prior to the description of the effects, a brief summary of the behavioral data as well as general neuromagnetic emergence pattern will be given.",
